1. To generate an llvm file from a give c file use the following command:
clang -S -emit-llvm (filename).c -o (filename).ll

2. To complile and generate a.out for your optimized llvm file use the 
following command:
clang (filename).ll main.c

3. Run the executable generated from both the optimized and the unoptimized 
llvm to compare the outputs.
 
